(c)  all sums from time to time received by or falling due to the 
Majlis in respect of the repayment of any loan made by the 
Majlis and the interest payable in respect of any such loan;

(e)  moneys  earned  or  arising  from  any  property,  investments, 
mortgages, charges or debentures acquired by or vested in 
the Majlis;

(d)  paying  any  other  expenses,  cost  or  expenditure  properly 
incurred or accepted by the Majlis in the execution of its duty 
or in the discharge of its functions under section 6;

(b)  wilfully applies any loan made to him by the Majlis under 
this Act to any purpose other than the purpose for which the 
loan was made;

(b)  prescribing  the  manner  in  which  documents,  cheques  and 
instruments of any description shall be signed or executed on 
behalf of the Majlis or any corporation;

(a)  from  time  to  time,  make  or  cause  to  be  made  such  enquiry  as  may  be 
necessary to ensure that the loan is being applied to the purpose for which 
it was made;
